  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-154517ec-7fff-7f0f-23af-7b69735b8e70&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;proposed second floor outrigger window,&amp;nbsp;by reason of its design and position, would result in new lines of sight and a loss of privacy and overlooking to neighbouring windows and their amenity space, resulting in an adverse impact on the living conditions of neighbouring occupiers. As such the proposed development is contrary to policy D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP2 (Development and amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained within&amp;nbsp;Council&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementation Planning Document (2009).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-8aa8a959-7fff-2d6b-3425-4e33eee67601&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed ground floor rear extension, by reason of its scale, height and bulk, would result in an overbearing and unneighbourly form of development that would have a harmful impact on the amenity of adjoining occupiers in terms of increased sense of enclosure, loss of daylight. and overshadowing As such, the proposal is contrary to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;policy LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained in the Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-182e289b-7fff-6ea3-e82c-a9a9cdc42ced&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed ground floor rear and outrigger roof extensions, by reason of their height, scale, massing and detailed design, would result in incongruous, overbearing and overly dominant additions that would not appear subservient to the host dwelling and adversely impact upon the character and appearance of the site and wider adjoining terrace. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies&amp;nbsp; D1 (London’s form, character, and capacity for growth), D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach), and D4 (Delivering good design) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained in the Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
